{"type":"message","id":"d0033b15","parentId":"3b096de6","timestamp":"2026-02-15T14:37:09.680Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 16:37 GMT+2] OPERATION: DOCKER IMMORTALITY.\n\n1.  **Spec-First Design:**\n    *   Create `specs/DOCKER_RESTRUCTURE.md`.\n    *   *Schema:* `bot-master` (Orchestrator), `bot-worker` (Scaled x4), `redis` (Cache/Queue).\n    *   *Optimization:* Multi-stage build (Builder -> Runner) for minimal size.\n\n2.  **Thinking Loop (Latency & Security):**\n    *   *Analysis:* Docker Bridge adds ~0.1-0.2ms overhead. `network_mode: host` removes this but is tricky on Windows Docker Desktop (VM layer).\n    *   *Solution:* Use `host` mode if possible, or highly optimized `bridge` with `sysctls` tuning.\n    *   *Secrets:* Use `docker secret` or `.env` file injection (avoid copying keys into image!).\n\n3.  **Infrastructure as Code:**\n    *   Create `Dockerfile`:\n        *   Base: `python:3.14-slim`.\n        *   Install `orjson`, `uvloop`, `nacl`.\n        *   Copy `src/` and `skills/`.\n    *   Create `docker-compose.yml`:\n        *   Services: `redis`, `master`, `worker-cs2`, `worker-rust`, etc.\n        *   Healthchecks: `curl localhost:8501/_stcore/health` or script check.\n        *   Volumes: `D:\\Dmarket_bot\\logs:/app/logs`.\n\n4.  **Output:**\n    *   Specs confirmation.\n    *   Thinking block summary.\n    *   Dockerfile & Compose content.\n    *   Ready message."}],"timestamp":1771166229678}}
{"type":"message","id":"abbda209","parentId":"d0033b15","timestamp":"2026-02-15T14:37:34.998Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Designing Docker Restructure**\n\nI'm presently focused on structuring the specifications for \"Docker Immortality\". I'm meticulously crafting `specs/DOCKER_RESTRUCTURE.md`. The design process is taking shape, and I'm detailing the schema and optimization elements, focusing on a spec-first approach to solidify the foundation.\n\n\n**Elaborating Specifications Further**\n\nI've been drilling down into the intricacies of the specs file. I'm currently defining the nuances of latency impacts tied to Docker networking modes, including a deep dive on Windows-specific considerations. I'm focusing on the trade-offs between Docker Bridge and Host modes, with a side quest on optimal secret management strategies. This is all being carefully written into `specs/DOCKER_RESTRUCTURE.md`.\n\n\n**Defining Architecture Details**\n\nI'm now deep-diving into the `Dockerfile` and `docker-compose.yml` configurations. I'm focusing on the multi-stage build structure for the Dockerfile and carefully mapping volumes and ports within the compose file. I will be sure to address the Windows networking nuances when addressing the network setup. I am planning on adding sysctls for improved performance based on the prompt.\n\n\n**Formulating Initial Plans**\n\nI'm now formulating the initial plan for restructuring the Docker environment. I'm focusing on the steps to be taken, and outlining the process of how to handle the prompt requirements. I'm setting up the environment checks, and then I will be tackling the core spec file and associated infrastructure-as-code files. I'm focusing on the Windows Docker Desktop networking constraint.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771166248166_290","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir specs"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771166251130_291","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# DOCKER RESTRUCTURE SPECIFICATION\n## 1. Architecture Schema\n- **Orchestrator (`bot-master`)**: Central command, handles signals and coordination.\n- **Workers (`bot-worker`)**: Scaled execution units (x4 replicas). specialized for tasks.\n- **Cache/Queue (`redis`)**: Fast ephemeral storage and message broker between Master and Workers.\n\n## 2. Optimization Strategy\n- **Multi-stage Build**: \n  - **Builder Stage**: Compiles dependencies, wheels, and prepares environment.\n  - **Runner Stage**: Minimal runtime image containing only compiled artifacts and source code.\n- **Size Goal**: < 200MB per image.\n\n## 3. Network & Latency (Windows Context)\n- **Challenge**: Docker Desktop on Windows runs inside a lightweight VM. `network_mode: host` does not bridge to the Windows host NIC directly, but to the VM's NIC.\n- **Strategy**: \n  - Use `bridge` mode.\n  - Apply `sysctls` tuning for TCP stack optimization to mitigate bridge overhead.\n  - Keep internal traffic (Master <-> Redis <-> Worker) within the Docker network (fastest).\n\n## 4. Security\n- **Secrets Management**: \n  - strict `.env` file injection.\n  - **NO** hardcoded secrets in Dockerfile.\n  - Redis password protected.\n","file_path":"specs/DOCKER_RESTRUCTURE.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771166254868_292","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"Dockerfile","content":"# Stage 1: Builder\nFROM python:3.14-slim as builder\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\n# Install system build deps\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \\\n    build-essential \\\n    gcc \\\n    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n\n# Install python heavy-hitters\n# Note: explicit versions recommended for prod, unpinned for now per spec\nRUN pip install --user --no-cache-dir orjson uvloop PyNaCl redis aiohttp\n\n# Stage 2: Runner\nFROM python:3.14-slim as runner\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\n# Copy installed packages from builder\nCOPY --from=builder /root/.local /root/.local\nENV PATH=/root/.local/bin:$PATH\n\n# Copy application source\nCOPY src/ /app/src/\nCOPY skills/ /app/skills/\n\n# Optimization: Pre-compile bytecode\nRUN python -m compileall .\n\n# Runtime config\nENV PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1\nENV PYTHONDONTWRITEBYTECODE=1\n\n# Healthcheck script placeholder (can be overridden in compose)\n# HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=10s --start-period=5s CMD curl -f http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1\n\nCMD [\"python\", \"src/main.py\"]\n"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771166254991_293","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"services:\n  redis:\n    image: redis:alpine\n    container_name: dmarket_redis\n    restart: always\n    command: redis-server --save 60 1 --loglevel warning\n    sysctls:\n      net.core.somaxconn: 1024\n    healthcheck:\n      test: [\"CMD\", \"redis-cli\", \"ping\"]\n      interval: 5s\n      timeout: 3s\n      retries: 5\n    networks:\n      - bot_net\n\n  master:\n    build: .\n    container_name: bot_master\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    command: python -m src.master\n    env_file:\n      - .env\n    volumes:\n      - D:\\Dmarket_bot\\logs:/app/logs\n    depends_on:\n      redis:\n        condition: service_healthy\n    networks:\n      - bot_net\n    sysctls:\n      net.ipv4.tcp_keepalive_time: 60\n\n  worker-cs2:\n    build: .\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    command: python -m src.worker --type cs2\n    deploy:\n      replicas: 2\n    env_file:\n      - .env\n    volumes:\n      - D:\\Dmarket_bot\\logs:/app/logs\n    depends_on:\n      - master\n      - redis\n    networks:\n      - bot_net\n\n  worker-rust:\n    build: .\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    command: python -m src.worker --type rust\n    deploy:\n      replicas: 2\n    env_file:\n      - .env\n    volumes:\n      - D:\\Dmarket_bot\\logs:/app/logs\n    depends_on:\n      - master\n      - redis\n    networks:\n      - bot_net\n\nnetworks:\n  bot_net:\n    driver: bridge\n    driver_opts:\n      com.docker.network.bridge.enable_icc: \"true\"\n","file_path":"docker-compose.yml"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":5205,"output":1936,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":7141,"cost":{"input":0.010409999999999999,"output":0.023232,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.033642}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771166229679}}
