{"type":"message","id":"bd2d8972","parentId":"89d7b64e","timestamp":"2026-02-15T14:37:46.885Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Assessing the Completion**\n\nI've confirmed the completion of all specified tasks. The files `specs/DOCKER_RESTRUCTURE.md`, `Dockerfile`, and `docker-compose.yml` have been successfully created. The Dockerfile utilizes a multi-stage build, a nice touch. I am now proceeding to the next stage.\n\n\n**Validating the Files**\n\nI am now meticulously verifying the files. The specification file and Dockerfile seem sound, with the base image, installations, and copy commands all matching the requirements. However, I need to add the healthcheck to the master service in `docker-compose.yml` to fully align with the prompt's request.\n\n\n**Refining the Docker-Compose**\n\nI've reviewed the files and noticed the omission of the healthcheck for the master service in `docker-compose.yml`. I'm now updating that file to include the healthcheck as specified in the prompt, using `curl localhost:8501/_stcore/health`. This should complete the required changes to the docker-compose file. Once done, the project will be ready.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"edit_1771166266880_294","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"docker-compose.yml","oldText":"  master:\n    build: .\n    container_name: bot_master\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    command: python -m src.master\n    env_file:\n      - .env\n    volumes:\n      - D:\\Dmarket_bot\\logs:/app/logs\n    depends_on:\n      redis:\n        condition: service_healthy","newText":"  master:\n    build: .\n    container_name: bot_master\n    restart: unless-stopped\n    command: python -m src.master\n    env_file:\n      - .env\n    volumes:\n      - D:\\Dmarket_bot\\logs:/app/logs\n    healthcheck:\n      test: [\"CMD\", \"curl\", \"-f\", \"http://localhost:8501/_stcore/health\"]\n      interval: 30s\n      timeout: 10s\n      retries: 3\n    depends_on:\n      redis:\n  